headline: Eaton selected by the United States Air Force Research Laboratory to design innovative aerial refueling system
summary: CLEVELAND, November 12, 2024--Intelligent power management company Eaton was awarded a $3.5M Air Force Research Lab (AFRL) contract to design a new podded refueling boom, enabling traditional and non-traditional tanker aircraft to perform safe in-flight refueling. Eaton received the contract from the AFRL Transformational Capabilities Office (TCO) after participation in the Air-to-Air Refueling Mechanism Digital Design Challenge by AFWERX, the innovation arm of the U.S. Department of the Air For
